c-stdio-note.content:
The stdio.h header provides printf and scanf for basic I/O.

Example:
#include <stdio.h>
int main() {
    printf("Hello, World!\n");
    return 0;
}

c-vars-note.content:
C requires explicit type declarations.

Example:
int age = 25;
float pi = 3.14;
char grade = 'A';
printf("Age: %d, Pi: %.2f, Grade: %c\n", age, pi, grade);

c-ifelse-note.content:
Use if-else for conditional execution.

Example:
int x = 10;
if (x > 5) {
    printf("Greater than 5\n");
} else {
    printf("5 or less\n");
}

sql-select-note.content:
Use SELECT to choose columns from a table.

Example:
SELECT name, grade FROM students WHERE grade = 'A';
